race.comment: FRENCH RIVIERA (4) resumes here but the form she showed when last in work was good enough for a race of this calibre. Tuned up for this with a recent trial placing and is drawn to get all the favours from the inside alley. Can run a big race while fresh. HIDDEN FUTURE (13) just ran into one better when facing the starter for the first time and will have derived a stack of benefit from that day at the races. Should be right there at the business end. CHAMPAGNE TOWER (1) has placed three of four around this circuit and looks to be working up to a maiden victory. Top-three candidate. WINGEANDWIN (15) wasn't disgraced on debut and Thompson sticks following that first-up effort. Respect from the Vandyke barn. DA VINCI GLOW (12) is at the races for the first time and is sure to be well-educated from the Freedman stable. Monitor market moves.
